President Donald J. Trump has authorized an increase in federal funding for debris removal and emergency protective measures in Puerto Rico following Hurricane Maria. The increase allows for 100 percent federal funding for debris removal and emergency protective measures, including direct federal assistance, for 180 days from the date of the declaration. For further information, media can contact the FEMA News Desk at (202) 646-3272 or FEMA-NEWS-DESK@FEMA.DHS.GOV.